text.section:
The Department shall:
Implement training for administrators and other personnel responsible for collecting, maintaining, analyzing, and publicly reporting data regarding four-year adjusted cohorts and graduation rates;
Implement a standard process for verifying the accuracy of data including:
Statistical checks and analyses; and
On-site audits of record-keeping procedures;
Implement a public awareness campaign including outreach to civic associations, community-based groups, and parent organizations and the solicitation of suggestions and community support regarding the need for collecting, maintaining, analyzing, and publicly reporting accurate data regarding four-year adjusted cohorts and graduation rates;
Provide technical support to the county boards with collecting, maintaining, analyzing, and publicly reporting graduation rate data; and
Serve as a central repository for this data.
